{"title_page": "Manushulanta Okkate", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Manushulanta Okkate\n| image          = Manushulanta Okkate.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| writer         = Dasari Narayana Rao<br />{{small|(screenplay / dialogues)}}\n| story          = V. Mahesh<br />R. K. Dharmaraj\n| producer       = Duddu Venkateswara Rao<br />V. Mahesh\n| director       = [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]\n| starring       = [[N. T. Rama Rao]]<br />[[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]]<br />[[Manjula Vijayakumar|Manjula]]\n| music          = [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n| cinematography = M. Kannappa\n| editing        = K. Balu\n| studio         = Aditya Chitra\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|1976|4|7}}\n| runtime        = 145 mins\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         =\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Manushulanta Okkate''''' ({{trans|All Humans are Equal}})  is a 1976 [[Telugu language]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]], produced by Duddu Venkateswara Rao and V. Mahesh under the Aditya Chitra banner and directed by [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]. It stars [[N. T. Rama Rao]], [[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]], [[Manjula Vijayakumar|Manjula]] in the lead roles and music composed by [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]. The film was recorded as a \"Super Hit\" at the box office.{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Plot==\nThe film narrates a story with a message of universal brotherhood and equality between the rich and poor, Sarvarayudu (Satyanarayana) is the Zamindar. His son Rajendra Babu (First NTR) grows with oppressive mind about the poor people. He is turned out to be good by Radha (Jamuna) when he wanted to spoil her. He joins the poor and fights against the Zamindar for the justice and marries Radha. They had a son Ramu (Second NTR). Zamindar got his son killed. His grandson Ramu teaches him the final lesson.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[N. T. Rama Rao]] as Rajendra Babu & Ramu (Dual role)\n*[[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]] as Radha\n*[[Manjula Vijayakumar|Manjula]] as Shanti \n*[[Kaikala Satyanarayana|Satyanarayana]] as  Sarvarayudu\n*[[Allu Ramalingaiah]] as Chalamaiah \n*[[Nagesh]] as Ganapati \n*[[Rajasree|Rajasri]]\n*[[Ramaprabha]] as  Mutyalu & Rama (Dual role)\n*Kakarala as Sundara Chary\n*[[Kommineni Seshagiri Rao]] \n*[[Chalapathi Rao]]\n\n==Crew==\n*'''Art''': Rajendra Kumar\n*'''Choreography''': Raju-Seshu\n*'''Stills''': Chitti Babu\n*'''Fights''': Sambasiva Rao\n*'''Lyrics''': [[Aatreya (playwright)|Acharya Aatreya]], [[C. Narayana Reddy]], [[Kosaraju Raghavaiah|Kosaraju]] \n*'''Playback''': [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]], [[P. Susheela]] \n*'''Music''': [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n*'''Story''': V. Mahesh, RK Dharmaraj\n*'''Editing''': K. Balu\n*'''Cinematography''': M. Kannappa \n*'''Producer''': Duddu Venkateswara Rao, V. Mahesh \n*'''Dialogues - Screenplay - Director''': [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]  \n*'''Banner''':  Aditya Chitra\n*'''Release Date''': 7 April 1976\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Manushulanta Okkate\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1976\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Soundtrack\n| length     =\n| label      = SAREGAMA Audio\n| producer   = [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\nMusic composed by [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]. All songs are hit tracks.  Music released by SAREGAMA Audio Company. \n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!S. No!!Song Title !!Lyrics !!Singers !!length\n|-\n|1\n|\"Anubhavinchu Raja\"\n|[[C. Narayana Reddy]]\n|[[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]]\n|3:41\n|-\n|2\n|\"Kaalam Kadu\"\n|[[Aatreya (playwright)|Acharya Aatreya]] \n|SP Balu \n|3:15\n|-\n|3\n|\"Muthyalu Vasthava\"\n|[[Kosaraju Raghavaiah|Kosaraju]]\n|SP Balu, [[P. Susheela]]\n|4:02\n|-\n|4\n|\"Ninne Pella