. It stars [[N. T. Rama Rao]], [[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]], [[Manjula Vijayakumar|Manjula]] in the lead roles and music composed by [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]. The film was recorded as a \"Super Hit\" at the box office.{{citation needed|date=June 2019}}\n\n==Plot==\nThe film narrates a story with a message of universal brotherhood and equality between the rich and poor, Sarvarayudu (Satyanarayana) is the Zamindar. His son Rajendra Babu (First NTR) grows with oppressive mind about the poor people. He is turned out to be good by Radha (Jamuna) when he wanted to spoil her. He joins the poor and fights against the Zamindar for the justice and marries Radha. They had a son Ramu (Second NTR). Zamindar got his son killed. His grandson Ramu teaches him the final lesson.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[N. T. Rama Rao]] as Rajendra Babu & Ramu (Dual role)\n*[[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]] as Radha\n*[[Manjula Vijayakumar|Manjula]] as Shanti \n*[[Kaikala Satyanarayana|Satyanarayana]] as  Sarvarayudu\n*[[Allu Ramalingaiah]] as Chalamaiah \n*[[Nagesh]] as Ganapati \n*[[Rajasree|Rajasri]]\n*[[Ramaprabha]] as  Mutyalu & Rama (Dual role)\n*Kakarala as Sundara Chary\n*[[Kommineni Seshagiri Rao]] \n*[[Chalapathi Rao]]\n\n==Crew==\n*'''Art''': Rajendra Kumar\n*'''Choreography''': Raju-Seshu\n*'''Stills''': Chitti Babu\n*'''Fights''': Sambasiva Rao\n*'''Lyrics''': [[Aatreya (playwright)|Acharya Aatreya]], [[C. Narayana Reddy]], [[Kosaraju Raghavaiah|Kosaraju]] \n*'''Playback''': [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam|SP Balu]], [[P. Susheela]] \n*'''Music''': [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n*'''Story''': V. Mahesh, RK Dharmaraj\n*'''Editing''': K. Balu\n*'''Cinematography''': M. Kannappa \n*'''Producer''': Duddu Venkateswara Rao, V. Mahesh \n*'''Dialogues - Screenplay - Director''': [[Dasari Narayana Rao]]  \n*'''Banner''':  Aditya Chitra\n*'''Release Date''': 7 April 1976\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Manushulanta Okkate\n| type       = film\n| artist     = [[Saluri Rajeswara Rao]]\n| cover      =\n| alt 