{"title_page": "Anthony McDonald (Scottish footballer)", "text_new": "{{short description|Scottish association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Anthony McDonald\n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|2001|3|17|df=true}}\n| birth_place = [[Kirkcaldy, Scotland]]\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| height = \n| currentclub = [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline Athletic]]\n| clubnumber = \n| youthyears1 = 2009\u20132011\n| youthclubs1 = Real Fife\n| youthyears2 = 2011\u20132012\n| youthclubs2 = [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]]\n| youthyears3 = 2012\u20132017\n| youthclubs3 = [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]]\n| years1 = 2017\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]]\n| caps1 = 17\n| goals1 = 0\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]] (loan)\n| years2 = 2019\n| caps2 = 8\n| goals2 = 1\n| pcupdate = 2 April 2020\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\u20132018\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national under-16 football team|Scotland U16]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 7\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Scotland national under-17 football team|Scotland U17]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| ntupdate = \n| image = \n| caption = Anthony McDonald for Hearts\n| years3 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline Athletic]] (loan)\n| goals3 = 0\n| caps3 = 1\n}}\n\n'''Anthony McDonald''' (born 17 March 2001) is a Scottish [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]], as a midfielder. He has previously played for [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]] and [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline Athletic]] on loan.\n\n== Career ==\n\n=== Heart of Midlothian ===\nHe made his first team debut for Hearts, aged 16, on 12 December 2017, playing from the start in a 2\u20130 win against [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] at [[Tynecastle Park]].<ref>http://www.talkingbaws.com/2017/12/video-16-year-old-anthony-mcdonald-produces-dynamite-assist-hearts-debut/</ref> McDonald provided the assist for the opening goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-match-reports/hearts-2-dundee-0-jambos-11684526|title=16-year-old Anthony McDonald stars in Jambos debut and wins man of the match|date=12 December 2017|website=dailyrecord.co.uk|publisher=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]]|accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe joined Hearts at under-14 level from [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]].<ref name=\"EEN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/sport/football/hearts/hearts-academy-laying-local-foundations-for-the-future-1-4405916|title=Hearts academy laying local foundations for the future|author=Barry Anderson|date=29 March 2017|publisher=Edinburgh Evening News|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> He was a member of the Scotland under-16 Victory Shield squad.<ref name=\"EEN\" />\n\n=== Inverness Caledonian Thistle (Loan) ===\nMcDonald moved on loan to [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]] in January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/hearts/in-full/hearts-midfielder-anthony-mcdonald-completes-loan-move-to-inverness-1-4862679|title=Hearts midfielder Anthony McDonald completes loan move to Inverness|website=www.scotsman.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-18}}</ref> While with Inverness he scored his first ever professional goal, in a 2\u20132 draw against [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/fp/sport/football/inverness-caledonian-thistle/1726595/caley-jags-on-brink-of-play-offs-after-late-leveller-at-morton/|title=Caley Thistle on brink of play-offs after late leveller at Morton|last=Andy Skinner|website=Press and Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Dunfermline Athletic (Loan) ===\nMcDonald moved on loan to [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline Athletic]] with fellow Hearts youngster, [[Harry Cochrane]], on 30 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.edinburghlive.co.uk/sport/football/harry-cochrane-anthony-mcdonald-join-16839973|title=Hearts midfield duo head to Fife on season-long loan|last=Pilcher|first=Ross|date=2019-08-30|website=edinburghlive|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> Following a lengthy time out with injuries, McDonald made his Dunfermline debut from the bench on 21 December 2019 in a loss to his former club, [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dafc.co.uk/fixture.php?SID=First%20Team&D=2019-12-21&ID=1207|title=Dunfermline Athletic Football Club|website=www.dafc.co.uk|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|21 December 2019|<ref name=\"soc\">{{Cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/anthony-mcdonald/519625/ |title= Anthony McDonald Stats |website=uk.soccerway.com |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Scottish Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]]\n||[[2017\u201318 Heart of Midlothian F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"AM17\">{{Soccerbase season|108748|2017|accessdate=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Scottish Premiership]]\n|13||0||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||14||0\n|-\n||[[2018\u201319 Heart of Midlothian F.C. season|2018\u201319]]\n|[[Scottish Premiership]]\n|3||0||0||0||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||0\n|-\n||[[2019\u201320 Heart of Midlothian F.C. season|2019\u201320]]\n|[[Scottish Premiership]]\n|1||0||1||0||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5||1\n|-\n